// SOURCE: Source Files/Intergrations/Fusion - Rust Replacements/Fusion Product Sheet- FUSION MCP v1.0
// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Product Guide: FUSION MCP v1.0Component ID: F-MCP-1.0Classification: Protocol / ToolingAuthor: AI Integration Team1. Vision & PurposeThe Model Context Protocol (MCP) v1.0 is the bridge between the Fusion runtime and AI-driven development tools. It allows an AI assistant to "read" the live state of a running application to provide surgical debugging and performance tuning.2. Technical ImplementationReplaces: Traditional Log-based debugging and GDB/LLDB ad-hoc scripts.Interface: A JSON-RPC based protocol exposed via a secure local socket.3. Data Providersfusion::mcp::runtime: Provides scheduler depth, core pinning info, and task latency histograms.fusion::mcp::memory: Provides arena saturation levels and fragment maps.fusion::mcp::flux: Provides ring buffer sequence numbers and producer/consumer lag metrics.4. Why this existsIn complex distributed systems, logs aren't enough. MCP allows the IDE to ask the runtime: "Why is task 402 delayed?" and get an answer based on real-time scheduler telemetry.
